~ v0.0.4: explore + color

make data = json("{\"name\": \"Sam\", \"pets\": [\"cat\", \"dog\"], \"age\": 3}")
for each line in explore(data):
    show line
~ expected: name = Sam / pets[0] = cat / pets[1] = dog / age = 3

show length(explore(data))            ~ 4
show contains(color("red", "x"), "x") ~ yes  (color wraps the text)
